You need to create an endpoint in your php e.g. create a file &quot;getSessionValue.php&quot; with following content:

```
&lt;?php
$key = $_GET[&#39;key&#39;];

isset($_SESSION[$key]) ? echo $_SESSION[$key] : echo &#39;&#39;;

```

In your react application, you need to make an ajax call to the this file:

for example: 

```
const getSessionValue = async (key) =&gt; {
  try {
    return await axios.get(`getSessionValue.php?key=${$key}`).data
  } catch (error) {
    return undefined
  }
}
```

This is a simple solution just add

    credentials: &#39;same-origin&#39;

to your AJAX request.

You can do the following **as long as [chromium supports Apps][1]**,

    (async () =&gt; {
      const browser = await puppeteer.launch({ headless: false, args: [&#39;--app=http://example.com&#39;] });
      const [page] = await browser.pages();
      await page.screenshot({path: &#39;example.png&#39;});
      await browser.close();
    })();

What&#39;s happening:

- The `--app=` argument will make it open in app mode (not fullscreen, no url bar, it&#39;s a window etc.).
- `browser.pages()` will return the current open pages in an array.


  [1]: https://developer.chrome.com/apps/about_apps

